This would be easier with adding a CSS class with the expected `background-color` and then comparing if a table row has four cells with that class.

This approach makes the logic easier to control and removes the need for `id`&#39;s. You may still use them if needed later on, but for this routine they are not required.

Within `mouseclick()` we check if the click element contains the expected CSS class and when it doesn&#39;t then we add it.

Then, within `check()`:

+ we store the table rows in an Array.
+ loop through the array
+ store all the cells, in the current row, with the expected CSS class
+ then the total count is 4 we alert the user

I have added a second row to the table so that you can test multiple rows.

